20002001.kpi_description: Gives us the number of TV product sales.

70140002.kpi_description: Provides daily counts of devices and WHiX Lite scores with a few further WHiX Lite assessments as dimensions.  The WHiX Lite categories are Good, Bad or Very Bad.  The category is derived from RDKV telemetry marker values and business rules that evaluate these.  The purpose of the WHiX Lite metric is to give a measure of device performance and connectivity.

20001001.kpi_description: Gives us numbers of active TV subscribers.  Weekly data taken from the Xcellence Hub. DIM1 tells us about the TV Service and can be Sky+, Sky Q or SOIP.  If it is SOIP DIM5 breaks that down into Stream or Glass customers.  DIM2 gives us a view of the set top box type devices the customer has.  DIM3 tells us about the broadband router the customer has (where supplied by Sky) and DIM4 tells about the broadband tech (technology) in place when Sky supplied.

10010.kpi_description: This KPI is a view of pre-active journeys from an Orders viewpoint.

40010.kpi_description: This KPI set gives us data around assurance sessions detailing Black, Red, Amber and Green outcomes, overrides and HCAs by Channel.

10030.kpi_description: This KPI set gives details of the provisioning process.  Dates are measured from the Order date

10020.kpi_description: This KPI set gives details of the provisioning process.  Dates are measured from the Activation date

30020.kpi_description: This KPI gives us details of broadband router performance for the day.

40030.kpi_description: This KPI set gives us details of Sky High Cost Actions resulting from assurance sessions.

40040.kpi_description: This KPI set gives us details of costs of High Cost Actions resulting from assurance sessions and hence the cost to keep customers up and running.

30060.kpi_description: This KPI set gives data for the QOE measures and calculates the overall QOE scores.

30010.kpi_description: This KPI gives us a number of key customer experience indicators, including retrains and speed issues .

30030.kpi_description: This KPI gives us details of in-home WiFi experience at 2.4 GHz.

30040.kpi_description: This KPI gives us details of in-home WiFi experience at 5 GHz.

40020.kpi_description: This KPI set gives us details of Open Reach High Cost Actions resulting from assurance sessions.

60010.kpi_description: This KPI tells us the number of customers requesting to churn, in progress and completing the churn process each day.

20010.kpi_description: This KPI gives us the number of broadband customers we have, each day, broken out by a number of useful dimensions. This baselines many of our other KPIs.

indicators_float.name: Total days as a broadband Sky customer (sum)
Total days on current broadband agreement (sum)

70140001.kpi_description: Gives us satisfaction scores from the Customer Satisfaction monthly survey.  Several dimensions are available for analysis.  Weighted scores are held in the Float 1 variable.
